# ── Step 52: MEMORY.md Fallback Rule + Erroneous Write Revert ────────────────────

:Step52NoMemoryMdWriteRule a schema:Action ;
    schema:name "Write Step 52 establishing MEMORY.md as read-only fallback + revert erroneous MEMORY.md entry"@en ;
    schema:description "After writing Step 51, the agent also wrote a 'File Operations' section to .claude/projects/…/memory/MEMORY.md — violating the principle that preferences.ttl is the sole canonical write target. User flagged: 'Why are you writing to memory.md, despite preferences.ttl's role?' and 'The point here is memory.md shouldn't be used if there arent issues with preferences.ttl'. Remediation: (1) Reverted the erroneous MEMORY.md 'File Operations' section per user approval ('Yes, put it in preferences'); (2) Added :step-noMemoryMdWrite (position 52) to preferences.ttl establishing MEMORY.md as a read-only fallback never to be written to unless preferences.ttl is genuinely inaccessible/corrupt; (3) Created companion howto/no-memory-md-write.ttl with 3 substeps: (a) preferences.ttl is sole canonical write target, (b) what MEMORY.md actually is (system-generated safety net, not agent-maintained), (c) when MEMORY.md CAN be touched (catastrophic fallback only). Also added :topicNoMemoryMdWrite to schema:about list and :agentBehaviorGuide schema:step list on preferences.ttl. Updated preferences.ttl schema:dateModified to 2026-06-15T13:10:00Z."@en ;
    schema:actionStatus schema:CompletedActionStatus ;
    schema:agent <https://www.linkedin.com/in/kidehen#this> ;
    schema:object <../preferences.ttl>, <../howto/no-memory-md-write.ttl> ;
    schema:startDate "2026-06-15T13:10:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime .
